title: YUCAIPA: Rollover leaves passengers trapped, prompts SigAlert (UPDATE)
text:
BY ALI TADAYON / STAFF WRITER
Published: Oct. 8, 2015 Updated: 8:05 a.m. YUCAIPA: Rollover leaves passengers trapped, prompts SigAlert (UPDATE) Print Photo Share Pin It More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT Related article Â» A rollover crash on the 10 in Yucaipa left at least one person trapped inside a car Thursday, Oct. 8.
The crash was reported at 7:13 a.m. on the westbound side of the 10 east of Oak Glen Road, according to a California Highway Patrol incident log. Witnesses said the car flipped and landed in a ditch off of the road, according to the log.
The crash shut down the No. 3 lane of the westbound 10, triggering a SigAlert. The lane was opened back up about 8 a.m.
While Cal Fire San Bernardino firefighters were en route to the crash scene, an off-duty firefighter stopped and attempted to help. However, the firefighter was unable to get the victims out of the car.
Witnesses saw the car get hit by another car when attempting to enter the fast lane on the 10. The driver of the car in the fast lane wouldn't let the other car in, and rear-ended it, according to the log.
This story is developing. Check back for more information.
